1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
What if saving one species could protect countless others?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,800
Meet umbrella species—organisms whose conservation can prevent the decline of many other species.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:13,200
These species serve as a shield, protecting entire ecosystems from collapse.

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,800
Think of the tiger.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Its protection means safeguarding the entire forest it roams.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,800
But here's the catch: balancing conservation efforts is complex and uncertain.

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,000
Not every umbrella species can carry the weight.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,800
Some may fail, leading to unexpected outcomes.

9
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,200
Curious about how we can help?

10
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,200
Explore conservation efforts around you!
